<br>
HOWEVER, to avoid these things getting all confuzzled by walls and doors and passersby (wasting water with phantom flushes) they have a very limited effective range.<br>
<br>
In the case of Mr. Pee, if he's a long-distance shooter, or just enjoys displaying his thang to his co-workers, he could have started outside of this range.  As a result, the sensor never &quot;fixed&quot; on him and didn't know that someone was actually taking a leak.<br>
<br>
In most cases, non-flushination is a directly related to a leaner (backwards or forwards, depending on the plumbing) who inadvertantly stays out of range while doing their bidness.<br>
